<DIV CLASS="largetext"><B>Buying more bandwidth</B></DIV>
<P>
<DIV CLASS="mediumtext">
Ok, most of you won't know but I run a small web design company called <A HREF="http://www.otn.co.uk/">On The Net</A>. GuildMagic was written because I love EverQuest and wanted to do something for my guild. GuildMagic is hosted on On The Net's server. It's a pretty beefy web server, plenty of disk and CPU. Until GuildMagic came along that server was very very bored indeed. A couple of customer sites were running there and they barely touched the CPU, the disks or the bandwidth.
<P>
Things have changed a little - and I'm happy they have. But if GuildMagic is going to continue to be as popular as it currently is (heck - I want to see it even MORE popular) then I'm going to need to buy more bandwidth. That's why I've decided that advertising is a necessary evil.
<P>
Many of you have already asked me the obvious question - "why didn't I have advertising from the start?". Well let's just say I didn't expect this kind of interest. It's exciting and a little scary to see the site taking off. I'm confident that most of you won't mind at all that I've included the adverts but I did want to explain my reasons.
<P>
Rest assured that I am listening to all your comments and suggestions and I'll be adding large chunks of new functionality as well as addressing the many minor improvements that need making.
<P>
Thank you all for your continued support. 
<P>
